HEADWORD: Proleg
<hw>Pro"leg</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>pro-</ets>
for, in place of + <ets>leg</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of
the fleshy legs found on the abdominal segments of the larv⟦ae⟧ of
Lepidoptera, sawflies, and some other insects. Those of Lepidoptera have
a circle of hooks. Called also <altname>proped</altname>,
<altname>propleg</altname>, and <altname>falseleg</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

